Following the reports of the Federal and State primary election of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) held across the states, the party had on Saturday rescheduled a repeat of primaries in Lagos, Imo, Benue and Kastina States to nominate candidates for the 2023 general elections. The National Working Committee (NWC) of the opposition party made the approval known in a statement issued by its National Publicity Secretary, Debo Ologunagba, in Abuja. According to the party, the approval of the repeat of the primaries followed very careful deliberations on the reports of the Electoral and Appeal Panels on the congresses of PDP in Lagos, Imo, Benue and Katsina States. -Advertisement- The party, however, approved Sunday, June 5 for the repeat primaries in Ahiazu and Orsu State Constituencies of Imo and Musawa, Dandume, and Zango Constituencies of Katsina State. Others are Oru East/Orsu/Orlu Federal Constituency of Imo and Kwande/Ushongo Federal Constituency of Benue. Also, Monday, June 6 has been scheduled for Lagos State House of Representatives Primaries (24 Federal Constituencies). The statement partly read, “Furthermore, Kaduna Central Senatorial District of Kaduna State, Enugu West Senatorial Districts of Enugu State, and Boki/Ikom Federal Constituency and Yakuur II State Constituency, both of Cross River earlier scheduled for Saturday, June 4 have been cancelled.” He, therefore, advised all party members in the affected states to take note of the new dates, adding that the changes were for the consideration of the affected states. POLL “All party members in the affected states should please take note,” the statement added.